  <body>
    <h2>
      Activities
    </h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Write down the equations of motion.
      </li>
      <li>
        Show that when <i>L</i> goes through 1 a bifurcation happens: the 
        number and stability of fixed points change.
      </li>
      <li>
        Check the previous result in the simulation.
      </li>
      <li>
        Since the oscillations are anisotropic and anharmonic, we expect the 
        orbit to be different from Lissajous curves. Check this around each 
        stable fixed point in the different cases.
      </li>
      <li>
        When <i>L</i> = 1 and the initial horizontal displacement is much 
        greater than the vertical one, which is the oscillation center? Why?
      </li>
    </ol>
  </body>
</html>

